textAnnotations.description:
Megan Thomas nat tight-lipped, muring
the sleeping ladwallader. Driver and
conductor peered ahead into nothingners.
On the back reat Itan Hayball embraced
his Eth. Morsydd thought of Dai. The
Rev. Edwards, standing at the front,
looked at his forlorn flock. "What
about a verse or two of Cwm Rhondda?"
he ruggented hopefully.
